"2071": {
    "id": 2071,
    "title": "Making Reprexes",
    "chapter_title": "Ch 8: Workflow: Getting Help",
    "content": "# â™»ï¸ Making Reprexes\n\n## Reprex = Reproducible Example\n\nIf you ask for help, you must provide code that others can run.\n\n1.  **Packages**: Load them at the top.\n2.  **Data**: Use built-in datasets like `mpg` or create small ones.\n3.  **Code**: Include the code that causes the error.\n\n## The `reprex` package\n\nRunning `reprex()` on your clipboard formats your code nicely for GitHub/StackOverflow.\n\n```r\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nmean(1:10)\n```\n\n---\n\n## ðŸŽ¯ Your Task\n\nWrite a minimal example that calculates the mean of numbers 1 to 5.\n",
    "starter_code": "# Minimal example\n",
    "solution_code": "mean(1:5)",
    "expected_output": "3",
    "chapter_id": 8
}